<font color="#ffff00">第五季 第五集</font>
<font color="#ffff00">S5E05</font>

5
00:01:47,970 --> 00:01:51,563
噢...天哪
Oh, my dear.

6
00:01:52,519 --> 00:01:55,190
最亲爱的
My dearest.

7
00:01:55,304 --> 00:01:57,879
我警告过你 我说过
I warned you, I said,

8
00:01:57,986 --> 00:02:00,229
千万不要走近悬崖
do not go to near the edge.

9
00:02:02,049 --> 00:02:05,029
你为什么推我 Baron?
Why did you push me Baron?

10
00:02:07,632 --> 00:02:11,183
我亲爱的太太 你是在做梦呢
Dear wife, you're dreaming.

11
00:02:11,184 --> 00:02:16,856
不 你撒谎...撒谎
No.You're lying.

12
00:02:19,647 --> 00:02:21,760
噢 我亲爱的
Oh, my darling.

13
00:03:02,367 --> 00:03:05,677
<font color="#ffff00">显贵的主顾</font>
<font color="#ffff00">The Illustrious Client</font>

14
00:03:12,823 --> 00:03:14,713
有什么激动人心的事吗 福尔摩斯?
Anything stirring Holmes?

15
00:03:16,201 --> 00:03:18,151
我了解的就这么多
I know no more than this.

16
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:23,298
也许是一个自大的傻胖子
There may be some fatty self-important fool,

17
00:03:23,335 --> 00:03:25,843
也许是一件生死攸关的事情
it may be a matter of life or death.

18
00:03:26,764 --> 00:03:28,718
嗯 你同意会面了?
Mmm, you grant this interview?

19
00:03:28,755 --> 00:03:30,556
我已经确认过了
I've already confirmed it.

20
00:03:30,593 --> 00:03:31,951
对于这个人你有什么了解吗?
Do you know anything of the man?

21
00:03:31,988 --> 00:03:34,421
只知道陆军上校James Damery爵士
Only that the name Colonel Sir James Damery

22
00:03:34,459 --> 00:03:36,057
是一个家喻户晓的名字
is a household word in society.

23
00:03:36,094 --> 00:03:38,243
我可以告诉你更多
I can tell you a little bit more than that.

24
00:03:38,691 --> 00:03:40,059
他擅长处理棘手而微妙的事情
He has rather the reputation

25
00:03:40,096 --> 00:03:41,648
因而名声在外
for arranging delicate matters,

26
00:03:41,685 --> 00:03:43,853
这些事情是不为媒体所知
which are to be kept out of the papers.

27
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:47,112
他举世闻名 在外交方面天赋过人
He's a man of the world with a natural turn for diplomacy.

28
00:03:47,354 --> 00:03:49,754
所以我们可以认为
And then, therefore to hope

29
00:03:49,791 --> 00:03:52,074
这不是一个错误的警报
it is not a false scent,

30
00:03:52,111 --> 00:03:55,983
他应该真的需要我们的帮助
that he has some real need of our assistance.

31
00:03:57,568 --> 00:03:58,878
我们?
Our?

32
00:03:59,657 --> 00:04:01,481
嗯 华生 要是你能好心帮帮忙的话
If you'll be so good Watson.

33
00:04:01,518 --> 00:04:03,419
我很荣幸
I shall be honored.

34
00:04:05,219 --> 00:04:06,740
那么在四点半以前
Then until four-thirty o'clock

35
00:04:06,777 --> 00:04:09,395
我们可以暂时把这事抛在脑后了
we can put the matter out of our heads.

36
00:04:14,505 --> 00:04:15,600
福尔摩斯先生
Mr. Holmes,

37
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:20,321
这次我们要对付的是欧洲最危险的人
we are dealing on this occasion with the most dangerous man in Europe.

38
00:04:20,358 --> 00:04:21,804
我曾经有几个对手
I've had several opponents 

39
00:04:21,805 --> 00:04:23,804
也可以被冠之以这样的称呼
to whom that flattering term has been applied.

40
00:04:23,841 --> 00:04:26,566
他是一个暴徒
A man to whom violence is familiar

41
00:04:26,566 --> 00:04:29,203
杀人不眨眼
and who will literally stick at nothing.

42
00:04:30,164 --> 00:04:30,974
您不抽烟吗?
Do you smoke?

43
00:04:31,001 --> 00:04:32,328
请原谅我抽烟
Excuse my pipe.

44
00:04:32,365 --> 00:04:34,314
要是您说的这个人
But if your man is more dangerous

45
00:04:34,351 --> 00:04:35,810
比已故的Moriarty教授还要危险
than the late Professor Moriarty,

46
00:04:35,847 --> 00:04:36,958
那他就真值得会上一会了
he's indeed worth meeting.

47
00:04:36,995 --> 00:04:38,202
他叫什么呢?
May I ask his name?

48
00:04:38,239 --> 00:04:40,834
您听说过Baron Gruner吗?
Have you ever heard of Baron Gruner?

49
00:04:42,354 --> 00:04:44,227
那个奥地利的杀人犯?
The Austrian murderer?

50
00:04:44,264 --> 00:04:47,042
那么您已经把他列为杀人犯了?
So you've already sized him up as a murderer?

51
00:04:47,079 --> 00:04:51,057
我们的业务就是关注欧洲大陆各种罪案
It is our business to follow the details of Continental crime.

52
00:04:51,094 --> 00:04:53,235
在Splugen隘道那起所谓的事故中
I'm sure that he killed his wife

53
00:04:53,272 --> 00:04:54,883
正是他杀了他的妻子
when that so called accident happened

54
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:57,377
对此我毫不怀疑 就像亲眼所见一般
at the Splugen Pass as if I'd seen him do it.

55
00:04:57,830 --> 00:04:58,961
我还肯定
Just as I am certain

56
00:04:58,997 --> 00:05:01,230
是他除掉了唯一的目击证人
that he disposed the only witness,

57
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:03,330
那个无辜的牧童
that innocent shepherd boy.

58
00:05:03,705 --> 00:05:05,991
Baron Gruner现在在英国
Baron Gruner is now in England.

59
00:05:06,785 --> 00:05:08,921
他听说他就住在Kingston附近?
Residing near Kingston I'm informed?

60
00:05:08,958 --> 00:05:10,466
没错
That is so.

61
00:05:10,503 --> 00:05:12,076
我想您应该
Might I also suppose

62
00:05:12,113 --> 00:05:14,652
也听说过Merville将军的名字吧?
you will have heard of General Merville?

63
00:05:15,821 --> 00:05:17,387
他以前是个风云人物
Khyber Pass fame.

64
00:05:18,219 --> 00:05:19,608
是的
Indeed,

65
00:05:20,302 --> 00:05:23,273
Merville将军有个女儿叫Violet
General Merville has a daughter, Violet.

66
00:05:23,310 --> 00:05:26,154
年轻 富有 多才多艺
Young, rich, accomplished,

67
00:05:26,190 --> 00:05:28,289
不管从哪方面看 都是个非凡的女孩儿
a wonder woman in every way.

68
00:05:28,327 --> 00:05:30,569
她是个单纯的孩子
It is she an innocent

69
00:05:30,606 --> 00:05:34,505
我们要努力把她从那个魔鬼手里救出来
we are endeavoring to save from the clutches of this fiend.

70
00:05:34,542 --> 00:05:36,144
他控制着她吗?
He has some hold over her?

71
00:05:36,180 --> 00:05:39,507
福尔摩斯先生 对女人最有力的控制就是...
The strongest of all where women are concerned, Mr. Holmes.

72
00:05:39,544 --> 00:05:42,705
哈 爱情
Ah, love.

73
00:05:42,742 --> 00:05:44,097
对极了
Exactly.

74
00:05:47,418 --> 00:05:49,282
亲爱的 要是我娶了你
In marrying you, my darling,

75
00:05:49,830 --> 00:05:52,672
我过去的罪恶就可以得到宽恕了
all my past sins shall be absolved.

76
00:05:52,709 --> 00:05:54,917
你告诉我的那些并不是什么罪恶
These aren't sins you've told me of.

77
00:05:55,654 --> 00:05:56,990
那些都是诽谤
These are slanders.

78
00:05:57,447 --> 00:05:58,394
我的天使
My angel.

79
00:05:58,432 --> 00:06:02,175
跟所有伟人一样 你当时被诱入歧途了
You were seduced, as are all great men.

80
00:06:02,212 --> 00:06:04,856
然而我还是决定让你知道我的过去
Yet I am determined you shall know my history,

81
00:06:04,893 --> 00:06:06,099
详详细细地
every part of it.

82
00:06:06,380 --> 00:06:08,019
那样的话 当我步上圣坛
Thus shall I come to the altar

83
00:06:08,056 --> 00:06:09,447
心境澄明
purified in soul and spirit

84
00:06:09,484 --> 00:06:13,862
最终我才对得起你的爱 对吧?
and worthy at last of your love?

85
00:06:13,899 --> 00:06:15,974
不过是六个星期
Just six weeks,

86
00:06:16,755 --> 00:06:18,493
噢 Adelbert
Oh Adelbert.

87
00:06:23,733 --> 00:06:26,470
我不能假装过去清白无暇
I cannot pretend my past is without stain.

88
00:06:27,348 --> 00:06:28,826
没有一个出身贫困
No man born in poverty

89
00:06:28,863 --> 00:06:30,887
而又白手起家的人可以那样说
who has created his own fortune

90
00:06:30,924 --> 00:06:32,991
说实话吧 不是的
can say that and speak the truth, oh, no.

91
00:06:33,028 --> 00:06:36,988
我曾经被迫做出不少无情的事情 亲爱的
I have been forced to many a ruthless act, my dear.

92
00:06:37,523 --> 00:06:39,311
我该从哪儿说起呢?
Where shall I begin?

93
00:06:42,184 --> 00:06:45,600
福尔摩斯先生 看到有人
To observe, Mr. Holmes, an atrocious event,

94
00:06:45,638 --> 00:06:47,654
就在您眼前谋划着一起残忍的罪行
preparing itself before your very eyes

95
00:06:47,691 --> 00:06:49,542
却无力改变它
and yet be powerless to avert it.

96
00:06:49,579 --> 00:06:52,430
还有任何人面对过
Could anyone, any human being

97
00:06:52,467 --> 00:06:54,721
比这更难受的事情吗?
be placed in a more trying position?

98
00:06:54,826 --> 00:06:55,934
也许没有
Perhaps not.

99
00:06:55,971 --> 00:06:59,764
那么您应该能够同情 我当事人的处境
Well then you will sympathize with the client in whose interest I am acting.

100
00:07:02,169 --> 00:07:03,212
我不明白
I did not understand

101
00:07:03,249 --> 00:07:05,499
您居然只是中间人
that you were merely an intermediary,

102
00:07:05,536 --> 00:07:07,577
那谁是委托人呢?
who is the principal?

103
00:07:08,135 --> 00:07:11,023
我恳求您不要问这个问题
I beg of you not to press that question.

104
00:07:11,061 --> 00:07:14,180
他的名字不能被牵扯进来
His name cannot be dragged into this matter.

105
00:07:14,217 --> 00:07:16,891
他的动机是非常高尚的
His motives are to the last degree honorable

106
00:07:16,928 --> 00:07:19,395
但是他不想让别人知道
but he prefers to remain unknown.

107
00:07:19,432 --> 00:07:23,547
而您的费用是不成问题 我可以保证 福尔摩斯先生
I need not say that your fees will be assured, Mr. Holmes.

108
00:07:27,553 --> 00:07:29,721
而且您不会受到任何约束
And you will be allowed a free hand.

109
00:07:32,254 --> 00:07:35,688
委托人的名字又有何相关呢?
Surely the actual name of your client is immaterial.

110
00:07:35,725 --> 00:07:38,271
我只能拒绝您的要求了 James爵士 我很抱歉
I must decline to act, Sir James, I'm sorry.

111
00:07:38,659 --> 00:07:41,016
我习惯了案件本身的迷雾重重
I'm accustomed to having mystery at one end of my cases

112
00:07:41,053 --> 00:07:43,599
但连您这边也是 未免太让人困惑了
but to have it at both ends is too confusing.

113
00:07:43,636 --> 00:07:44,700
不行
No.

114
00:07:47,034 --> 00:07:50,763
您让我太为难了
You place me in the most serious dilemma.

115
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:51,946
福尔摩斯先生
Dare I say, Mr. Holmes,

116
00:07:51,983 --> 00:07:54,988
我得说您没有意识到您这样做的后果
you hardly realize the affect of your own action.

117
00:07:55,544 --> 00:07:56,653
我保证过
I have given my word

118
00:07:56,654 --> 00:07:59,869
不泄露我当事人的名字
 not to reveal the identity of my client.

119
00:08:00,633 --> 00:08:04,259
能否允许我至少把可以讲的事 先告诉您?
May I at the least lay all I can before you?

120
00:08:16,245 --> 00:08:18,120
您必须明白
It is understood.

121
00:08:18,230 --> 00:08:19,411
我没有做出任何承诺
I commit myself to nothing.

122
00:08:19,448 --> 00:08:22,139
那是当然 我明白
But of course, yes, yes.

123
00:08:24,708 --> 00:08:26,498
画得太像了
A perfect likeness.

124
00:08:27,911 --> 00:08:29,055
是谁画的?
Who painted it?

125
00:08:29,164 --> 00:08:30,568
Innsbruck的Hans
Hans of Innsbruck,

126
00:08:30,606 --> 00:08:33,972
他是雕刻家Claus的后代 以雕刻铜像而著称
a descendant of Claus the sculptor famous for his bronzes

127
00:08:34,009 --> 00:08:35,499
就像这尊
such as this.

128
00:08:35,536 --> 00:08:42,122
我将委托Hans来为你 画一幅肖像 我亲爱的
I shall commission Hans to attempt your likeness, my precious.

129
00:08:42,159 --> 00:08:44,737
我爱这个房间
I love this room.

130
00:08:45,706 --> 00:08:48,092
到处都有你的气息
It breathes of you.

131
00:08:55,304 --> 00:08:57,123
这是什么呀?
What's this?

132
00:08:58,125 --> 00:09:00,069
你的日记吗?
Your diary?

133
00:09:00,658 --> 00:09:02,390
不 不 它是...
No, no, it is,

134
00:09:03,109 --> 00:09:05,495
是我的日常记事本
it is my commonplace book.

135
00:09:05,532 --> 00:09:08,173
里面记录着我看过的
In it I record things I've seen,

136
00:09:08,210 --> 00:09:09,377
读过的和欣赏的东西
read, admired,

137
00:09:09,415 --> 00:09:11,535
也许有时还有
occasionally perhaps

138
00:09:11,572 --> 00:09:13,940
我的一点儿想法
a thought or two of my own.

139
00:09:13,976 --> 00:09:16,517
但是它上了锁
But it's locked.

140
00:09:16,907 --> 00:09:18,692
它代表我的一部分
It is a little part of me,

141
00:09:18,729 --> 00:09:22,960
何况 我怕仆人会偷窥
besides a servant might pry.

142
00:09:22,997 --> 00:09:25,414
有一天 也许...
One day, perhaps,

143
00:09:26,132 --> 00:09:28,654
我们可以一起读一读
we shall look at it together.

144
00:09:28,691 --> 00:09:33,480
不 我尊重你的隐私 亲爱的
No, I respect your privacy, my darling.

145
00:09:33,517 --> 00:09:36,034
无论我们分享多少
We must all keep something of our own,

146
00:09:36,758 --> 00:09:39,156
总该有一些自己保留的东西
however much else we share.

147
00:09:41,268 --> 00:09:45,551
你真是太完美了
You are perfect.

148
00:09:48,046 --> 00:09:50,349
你应该教我一些瓷器的知识 Adelbert
You must teach me about porcelain, Adelbert.

149
00:09:50,386 --> 00:09:51,593
好的
I shall.

150
00:09:52,011 --> 00:09:53,912
收藏是一大乐事
Collecting is such a pleasure,

151
00:09:53,949 --> 00:09:55,498
赏心悦目
such a delight,

152
00:09:55,536 --> 00:09:56,885
总能让我充满激情
it is a passion with me

153
00:09:56,922 --> 00:09:59,594
就像你一样 我亲爱的
just as you are, my precious.

154
00:10:00,578 --> 00:10:02,558
这个恶棍黏上了这位女士
The villain has attached himself to a lady

155
00:10:02,595 --> 00:10:03,300
而且是彻彻底底
with such effect that he has completely 

156
00:10:03,301 --> 00:10:07,144
赢得了她的芳心
and absolutely won her heart.

157
00:10:07,181 --> 00:10:09,781
对他不利的话她一句也不想听
She will not hear one word against him.

158
00:10:09,818 --> 00:10:13,162
总而言之 她打算下个月就要嫁给他
To sum up, she proposes to marry him next month.

159
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:15,650
她已经成年了而且意志坚决
As she of age and has a will of iron

160
00:10:15,687 --> 00:10:18,396
真不知道如何阻止她
that's hard to know how to prevent her.

161
00:10:19,878 --> 00:10:21,566
这个被爱冲昏头脑的女士
Does the infatuated young woman

162
00:10:21,603 --> 00:10:23,190
知道发生在瑞士的那件事情吗?
know of the Swiss episode?

163
00:10:23,227 --> 00:10:23,981
这个狡诈的恶魔
The cunning devil

164
00:10:23,982 --> 00:10:26,890
把他过去所有令人厌恶的丑事都告诉了她
 has told her every unsavory scandal of his past life

165
00:10:26,927 --> 00:10:28,566
可是总把自己说成是
but always in such a way

166
00:10:28,603 --> 00:10:31,721
无辜的受害者
as to make himself out to be the innocent martyr.

167
00:10:32,301 --> 00:10:33,667
她完全听信于他
She accepts his version

168
00:10:33,704 --> 00:10:34,819
别人的话也不听
and will listen to no one,

169
00:10:34,856 --> 00:10:36,796
连长辈们的话也听不进去
not even her fathers.

170
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:38,046
天哪 James爵士
Dear me, Sir James,

171
00:10:38,083 --> 00:10:41,924
您是不是不小心泄露了 你的委托人的名字?
have you not inadvertently let out the name of your client?

172
00:10:41,961 --> 00:10:42,951
将军吗?
The General?

173
00:10:42,988 --> 00:10:44,487
噢 不 华生医生
Oh no, Dr. Watson,

174
00:10:45,008 --> 00:10:48,866
那位坚强的军人受此打击 已经一蹶不振了
that strong soldier has been utterly demoralized by this incident.

175
00:10:54,959 --> 00:10:56,312
MHudson太太
Mrs. Hudson.

176
00:10:56,349 --> 00:10:57,458
您摁铃了吗 先生?
You rang, sir?

177
00:10:57,495 --> 00:10:59,803
能不能麻烦你把这个 送到街角屠夫家的男孩那儿?
Will you deliver this to the butcher's boy around the corner?

178
00:10:59,841 --> 00:11:02,205
那个一只眼睛长得很可笑的小坏蛋吗?
That young rascal with the funny eye?

179
00:11:02,242 --> 00:11:05,410
另一只眼睛却是无价之宝啊 还有他的自行车
The other is invaluable, so is his bicycle.

180
00:11:05,895 --> 00:11:07,322
好的 先生
Sir.

181
00:11:14,474 --> 00:11:17,216
我该怎么联系您呢 James爵士?
How may I keep in touch with you, Sir James?

182
00:11:17,329 --> 00:11:18,442
您接受我的委托了吗?
You accept my commission?

183
00:11:18,548 --> 00:11:22,646
不妨说是您的问题引起了我的兴趣
Let us just say that your problem interests me.

184
00:11:22,762 --> 00:11:24,499
通过Carlton俱乐部可以找到我
The Carlton Club will find me.

185
00:11:24,608 --> 00:11:26,972
Baron在Kingston的具体地址是什么?
And the Baron's exact address in Kingston?

186
00:11:27,009 --> 00:11:28,074
Vernon宅邸
Vernon Lodge,

187
00:11:28,112 --> 00:11:29,544
一座大宅
the large house,

188
00:11:29,581 --> 00:11:30,870
他是个有钱人
he's a rich man.

189
00:11:30,908 --> 00:11:34,645
啊哈 投机者在成功的时候都是有钱人 James爵士
Uh-huh, speculators when successful frequently are, Sir James,

190
00:11:34,682 --> 00:11:35,880
您还能提供
what further information

191
00:11:35,916 --> 00:11:37,389
更多有关这个人的信息吗?
can you give us about the man?

192
00:11:37,426 --> 00:11:39,019
他的嗜好所费不菲
He has expensive tastes.

193
00:11:39,057 --> 00:11:40,588
收藏书籍 绘画
Collects books, pictures,

194
00:11:40,624 --> 00:11:42,331
噢 还有中国瓷器
oh, and Chinese pottery.

195
00:11:42,368 --> 00:11:44,285
他是这方面公认的权威
He's a recognized authority,

196
00:11:44,322 --> 00:11:46,622
写过一本相关的书
written a book upon the subject.

197
00:11:46,659 --> 00:11:48,358
James爵士 您可以告诉您的委托人
Well, Sir James, you may tell your client

198
00:11:48,394 --> 00:11:51,004
我会开始注意Baron Gruner的
that I'm turning my attention towards Baron Gruner.

199
00:11:51,041 --> 00:11:53,082
福尔摩斯先生 我毫不怀疑
I have no doubt, Mr. Holmes,

200
00:11:53,119 --> 00:11:55,547
您不费吹灰之力就可以 追查出我的委托人的身份
you can easily trace my client.

201
00:11:55,584 --> 00:11:57,593
但我必须请求您以名誉担保
But I must ask you as a point of honor

202
00:11:57,630 --> 00:11:59,997
请您不要这样做
to refrain from doing so.

203
00:12:00,033 --> 00:12:04,320
不要去挖出他的名字
Do not, I beg you, break in upon his incognito.

204
00:12:04,357 --> 00:12:05,967
我想这点我可以保证
I think I can safely promise that.

205
00:12:06,004 --> 00:12:07,411
谢谢
Thank you.

206
00:12:07,688 --> 00:12:09,514
再见 医生
Dr. Watson.

207
00:12:29,972 --> 00:12:32,092
你这是在浪费时间 华生
You're wasting your time, Watson.

208
00:12:32,096 --> 00:12:33,542
Merville将军的生涯
Now the career of General Merville

209
00:12:33,579 --> 00:12:35,688
也许正好帮我们查出我们委托人的身份
might well give us a pointer as to our client.

210
00:12:35,725 --> 00:12:36,889
他是如此杰出
He's clearly illustrious.

211
00:12:36,926 --> 00:12:38,141
但是您没有听到James爵士说的话吗?
But did you not hear, Sir James?

212
00:12:38,179 --> 00:12:40,581
他要求的是你 福尔摩斯
His request was to you, Holmes.

213
00:12:40,618 --> 00:12:42,517
这样做不光彩 华生 不光彩
But that is shameful, Watson, shameful

214
00:12:42,554 --> 00:12:48,108
再说我们的脑子要用在更有价值的地方 打消这念头吧
besides our minds should be  more gainfully employed, desist.

215
00:12:52,449 --> 00:12:54,318
对这件事你有什么看法吗?
Any views?

216
00:12:54,355 --> 00:12:55,448
你没有吗?
Have you none?

217
00:12:55,485 --> 00:12:56,850
还没有
Not yet.

218
00:12:57,439 --> 00:12:59,430
只有一个想法 我已经着手行事了
Beyond the one I've already acted upon.

219
00:12:59,466 --> 00:13:00,877
屠夫家的男孩
The butcher's boy.

220
00:13:00,914 --> 00:13:04,042
这样做比发电报谨慎
More discreet than any telegraph.

221
00:13:05,433 --> 00:13:10,028
嗯 我倒是觉得 你最好亲自去见见这位年轻女士
Well, I shall think you better see the young lady yourself.

222
00:13:10,065 --> 00:13:11,672
从她入手
Start with her.

223
00:13:11,709 --> 00:13:13,848
呃 要是那可怜的崩溃了的父亲 都不能说服她
Well, if her poor broken down father cannot move her,

224
00:13:13,885 --> 00:13:15,986
我这样一个陌生人又怎能成功呢?
how can I, a complete stranger prevail?

225
00:13:16,023 --> 00:13:17,603
呃 要是所有做法都不行
Well, if all else fails,

226
00:13:18,773 --> 00:13:20,024
也许我会去的
Perhaps.

227
00:13:20,572 --> 00:13:24,407
但是首先要利用下层社会
But first, the underworld.

228
00:13:25,020 --> 00:13:26,700
因为他们能接触到犯罪的邪恶本质
For it is among the dark roots of crime

229
00:13:26,737 --> 00:13:29,247
我们必须搜寻Gruner的秘密
that we must hunt for Gruner's secrets.

230
00:13:32,670 --> 00:13:34,923
你已经派人去找Shinwell Johnson了 (福尔摩斯在伦敦黑社会里的一个耳目)
You've sent for Shinwell Johnson.

231
00:13:36,027 --> 00:13:37,850
我有一个想法
I have but one insight,

232
00:13:39,247 --> 00:13:42,156
Merville小姐也许能够宽恕谋杀
that Ms. Merville might well condone murder

233
00:13:43,158 --> 00:13:48,000
但不会原谅某些更小的风流韵事
yet some smaller affair that might (unintelligible)

234
00:13:50,305 --> 00:13:51,696
我们走着瞧吧
We shall see.

235
00:13:55,326 --> 00:13:58,102
他们请到了最好的侦探
They have engaged the very best.

236
00:14:00,235 --> 00:14:01,539
让他进来
Show him in.

237
00:14:07,235 --> 00:14:10,089
这位是歇洛克.福尔摩斯先生  先生
Mr. Sherlock Holmes, sir.

238
00:14:18,657 --> 00:14:24,126
我早知道我们迟早会见面 福尔摩斯先生
I rather thought I should see you sooner or later, Mr. Holmes.

239
00:14:30,149 --> 00:14:33,079
你肯定是受到了Merville将军的委托吧
You've been retained no doubt by General Merville

240
00:14:33,116 --> 00:14:36,970
来阻止我和他女儿Violet的婚事
to prevent my marriage with his daughter, Violet?

241
00:14:39,415 --> 00:14:41,827
是这样的吧?
That is so, is it not?

242
00:14:47,213 --> 00:14:49,671
福尔摩斯先生 我竭力劝告您
Let me advise you very strongly, Mr. Holmes,

243
00:14:49,709 --> 00:14:51,275
就此罢手
to draw off at once.

244
00:14:51,312 --> 00:14:52,970
罢手?
Draw off?

245
00:14:53,830 --> 00:14:54,450
亲爱的朋友
My dear man,

246
00:14:54,488 --> 00:14:56,749
那不仅会毁掉你的好名声
you'll only ruin your well-deserved reputation.

247
00:14:56,786 --> 00:15:00,280
在这件事情上 你是没有希望成功的 罢手吧 先生
This is not a case in which you  can possibly hope to succeed, draw off sir.

248
00:15:00,950 --> 00:15:04,387
听上去有些奇怪 不过这也正是我要给你的忠告
It is curious but that is the very advice that I've come to give you.

249
00:15:05,185 --> 00:15:07,220
我坦率地说了吧
Let me put it to you man to man.

250
00:15:07,446 --> 00:15:08,978
如果你坚持要缔结这桩婚事
If you persist in this marriage,

251
00:15:09,015 --> 00:15:12,257
你将会树起无数劲敌
you will raise such a swarm of powerful enemies,

252
00:15:12,294 --> 00:15:14,296
到时连在英国的立足之地都没有
England would be too hot to hold you.

253
00:15:16,103 --> 00:15:19,037
你就此罢手将会是更明智的做法
Surely you will be wiser to draw off.

254
00:15:23,369 --> 00:15:26,090
原谅我的忍俊不禁 福尔摩斯先生
Excuse my amusement, Mr. Holmes,

255
00:15:26,128 --> 00:15:27,534
手上没有牌
but it really is very funny

256
00:15:27,571 --> 00:15:30,941
却想赌上一把 这实在太滑稽了
seeing you trying to play a hand with no cards in it.

257
00:15:30,978 --> 00:15:32,660
连一张大牌都没有 先生
Not a color card there, sir,

258
00:15:32,697 --> 00:15:34,305
除了小之又小的牌 你什么也没有
nothing but the smallest of the small.

259
00:15:34,342 --> 00:15:35,066
你自以为
So you think.

260
00:15:35,102 --> 00:15:36,909
不是'认为' 先生 是'知道'
So I know, sir, so I know.

261
00:15:36,947 --> 00:15:38,470
让我明白地告诉你
Let me make the thing clear to you.

262
00:15:38,507 --> 00:15:40,324
你觉得自己胜券在握
You consider your hand so strong

263
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:42,309
让我看见了也无妨吗?
that you could afford to show it?

264
00:15:42,347 --> 00:15:44,764
当然了 因为事情是明摆着的
Certainly, since it becomes plain that in this instance

265
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:47,113
在这件事上你完全无能为力 福尔摩斯先生
you are clearly out of your depth, Mr. Holmes.

266
00:15:47,519 --> 00:15:51,863
有没有可能你的能力被夸大了呢?
Could it be that your capabilities have been subject to hyperbole?

267
00:15:53,345 --> 00:15:55,540
你的一手牌呢 给我看吧
Your hand, show it.

268
00:15:56,105 --> 00:15:57,890
你不坐下来吗?
Won't you sit down?

269
00:15:58,712 --> 00:16:00,287
我想还是不要了
I think I shan't.

270
00:16:02,712 --> 00:16:04,015
那就随你的便
Please yourself.

271
00:16:08,502 --> 00:16:09,691
呃 先生
Well, sir,

272
00:16:11,313 --> 00:16:14,615
我碰巧就是很走运
it happens I have been fortunate enough

273
00:16:14,727 --> 00:16:18,626
赢得了Merville小姐全心的爱
to win the entire affection of Ms. Merville.

274
00:16:18,627 --> 00:16:19,832
尽管我曾经清楚地对她讲过
This in spite of the fact

275
00:16:19,869 --> 00:16:22,311
过去发生在我身上的
that I have informed her clearly

276
00:16:22,347 --> 00:16:27,916
所有那些不令人愉快的事件
of all the unhappy incidents in my past.

277
00:16:28,934 --> 00:16:32,831
我还警告她说 某些耍阴谋的人会去找她
I have warned her that certain  designing persons would come to her.

278
00:16:33,322 --> 00:16:35,921
我希望你认清这一点
I hope you recognize yourself in this

279
00:16:36,039 --> 00:16:38,426
并把这些事情告诉她
and would tell her of these things.

280
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:43,049
我已经教过她如何来对付这些事情
I have instructed her how to treat them.

281
00:16:44,639 --> 00:16:46,555
她对你的拜访已经做好准备了
She is well prepared for you.

282
00:16:50,804 --> 00:16:53,015
她肯定会答应见你
She will no doubt give you an appointment

283
00:16:53,937 --> 00:16:55,611
而且听完你的陈述
and she will listen.

284
00:16:57,073 --> 00:16:58,976
但你的所作所为都是徒劳
It will be to no avail, however.

285
00:17:02,331 --> 00:17:03,482
要是你想说些什么
If you wish to speak,

286
00:17:03,518 --> 00:17:05,713
现在正是时候
now is your moment.

287
00:17:07,590 --> 00:17:08,836
不
No,

288
00:17:10,027 --> 00:17:11,691
还不到时候
this is not the moment.

289
00:17:14,762 --> 00:17:17,334
顺便说一句 福尔摩斯先生
Oh, by the way, Mr. Holmes,

290
00:17:18,071 --> 00:17:21,991
你认识法国侦探Labrun吗?
did you know the French Agent Labrun?

291
00:17:22,076 --> 00:17:22,893
当然认识
Of course.

292
00:17:23,507 --> 00:17:25,210
那你也知道他出了什么事情吧?
So you know what befell him?

293
00:17:25,247 --> 00:17:28,239
他在巴黎的Lamont区遭到了毒打
He was beaten in the Lamont District of Paris

294
00:17:28,275 --> 00:17:30,078
落下了终生残废
and crippled for life.

295
00:17:30,115 --> 00:17:30,841
没错
Quite so.

296
00:17:30,878 --> 00:17:32,389
奇怪的巧合是
By an odd coincidence

297
00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:34,645
他之前同样在调查我
he had been inquiring into my affairs.

298
00:17:34,682 --> 00:17:38,842
还是别那样做的好 福尔摩斯先生 那样做不吉利
Don't do it, Mr. Holmes, it's not a lucky thing.

299
00:17:38,879 --> 00:17:40,400
我的最后忠告是...
My last word to you is

300
00:17:40,401 --> 00:17:44,562
你走你的阳关道 我走我的独木桥吧
 you go your way,let me go mine.

301
00:17:46,248 --> 00:17:47,970
好自为之吧 Gruner
Mind you Gruner,

302
00:17:48,622 --> 00:17:51,185
如果你指望为英国社交界所接受
because if you aspire to be accepted into English Society

303
00:17:51,222 --> 00:17:52,613
你就要学会在点雪茄之前
you'll do well to remove the band

304
00:17:52,649 --> 00:17:54,365
先把外头的标签去掉
from your Havana before lighting it

305
00:17:54,403 --> 00:17:57,784
否则人家会把你当成一个暴发户而瞧不起你
otherwise you'll be put down for a bounder.

306
00:18:11,491 --> 00:18:13,381
Hudson太太 福尔摩斯回来了吗?
Mrs. Hudson, has Holmes returned?

307
00:18:13,417 --> 00:18:16,492
还没呢 先生 不过有两个客人在等着
Not yet, sir, but there are two visitors waiting.

308
00:18:16,832 --> 00:18:18,596
谢谢 Hudson太太
Thank you, Mrs. Hudson.

309
00:18:25,071 --> 00:18:26,091
啊 Johnson
Why Johnson.

310
00:18:26,128 --> 00:18:27,101
晚上好 医生
Evening, Doctor,

311
00:18:27,139 --> 00:18:28,554
福尔摩斯先生给我捎话了
Mr. Holmes sent word to me.

312
00:18:28,590 --> 00:18:29,488
我知道 Johnson 我知道
I know, Johnson, I know.

313
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:31,073
我还把Kit带来了 因为...
And I brought Kit here because...

314
00:18:31,111 --> 00:18:32,552
我在博物馆耽搁了一会儿
That's when I was delayed at the museum

315
00:18:32,589 --> 00:18:34,713
然后又是交通
and then the traffic,

316
00:18:34,750 --> 00:18:37,719
有辆马车在Great Russell街翻车了
an omnibus overturned on Great Russell Street,

317
00:18:37,756 --> 00:18:40,057
他们得拖走两匹死马
two dead a horse had to be put down.

318
00:18:40,094 --> 00:18:41,100
请原谅 先生们
Gentlemen forgive me,

319
00:18:41,136 --> 00:18:43,185
我沉浸在自己的谜题中
I was absorbed by the mysteries of me,

320
00:18:43,223 --> 00:18:45,711
而忘记了时间 女士
I quite forgotten the hour, madam.

321
00:18:46,485 --> 00:18:48,012
这是Winter小姐 福尔摩斯先生
This is Ms. Winter, Mr. Holmes,

322
00:18:48,050 --> 00:18:49,114
我们叫她Kitty
Kitty we call her

323
00:18:49,151 --> 00:18:50,453
对于Gruner她没有什么不知道的
and what she don't know about Gruner.

324
00:18:50,490 --> 00:18:52,038
当然了 请讲吧
Of course, please.

325
00:18:52,075 --> 00:18:53,609
呃 Kitty自己可以讲
Well, Kitty can speak for herself.

326
00:18:53,646 --> 00:18:55,611
不管怎么说 一接到您的口信
Anyway I put me hand right on her

327
00:18:55,648 --> 00:18:56,991
一个钟头之内我就找到她了 先生
within an hour of your message, sir.

328
00:18:57,027 --> 00:18:58,535
很容易就能找到我
I'm easy to find.

329
00:18:58,572 --> 00:19:01,213
该死的 伦敦次次都让我犯迷糊
Hell, London gets me every time,

330
00:19:01,250 --> 00:19:02,873
小胖也是
same address goes for Porky.

331
00:19:02,910 --> 00:19:06,187
小胖? 那是你的外号吗 Johnson?
Porky, is that your nom-de-guerre Johnson?

332
00:19:06,224 --> 00:19:08,098
你可从没说起过
You have never revealed that.

333
00:19:08,135 --> 00:19:10,652
小胖 哈哈哈
Porky, well.

334
00:19:10,689 --> 00:19:13,566
小胖和我是老相识了
We're old mates, Porky and me.

335
00:19:13,603 --> 00:19:16,747
但是还有一个人 该下到比我们更深的地狱去
But there's someone who ought to be down in a lower hell than us

336
00:19:16,784 --> 00:19:18,891
那个人就是你在调查的人  福尔摩斯先生
and that's the man you're after, Mr. Holmes.

337
00:19:18,928 --> 00:19:20,746
我想我们能得到你帮助的吧 Winter小姐?
I gather we have your good wishes, Ms. Winter?

338
00:19:20,782 --> 00:19:22,564
要是我能帮上忙让他露出原形
If I can help put him where he belongs,

339
00:19:22,601 --> 00:19:25,591
我任您差遣 先生
I'm yours to the rattle, sir.

340
00:19:25,628 --> 00:19:26,735
你知道他的企图
Do you know what he intends,

341
00:19:26,772 --> 00:19:28,895
和目前的情况吗?
how the matter stands?

342
00:19:29,416 --> 00:19:31,968
小胖说他又追上了某个可怜的傻瓜
Porky tells me he's after some other poor fool

343
00:19:32,005 --> 00:19:34,851
只不过这次他想娶她
only this time he wants to marry her

344
00:19:34,888 --> 00:19:35,848
而您想阻止他?
and you want to stop it?

345
00:19:35,884 --> 00:19:37,225
是的
Yes.

346
00:19:37,262 --> 00:19:39,513
您对这个恶棍肯定有足够的了解
Surely you know enough about this devil

347
00:19:39,550 --> 00:19:41,250
去阻止任何头脑清醒的正派女子
to prevent any decent girl in her senses

348
00:19:41,286 --> 00:19:42,935
陷入与他的纠葛之中
wanting to have anything to do with him.

349
00:19:42,972 --> 00:19:45,582
可是她现在脑子并不清醒 Winter小姐
But she's not in her senses, Ms. Winter,

350
00:19:45,619 --> 00:19:46,678
她狂热地爱着他
she's madly in love

351
00:19:46,715 --> 00:19:49,325
而且她也听说过他的那些事了
and she has been told all about it.

352
00:19:49,361 --> 00:19:50,225
可是她不在乎
She cares for nothing.

353
00:19:50,262 --> 00:19:52,552
她也知道他杀过自己的妻子吗?
Told about the murder of his wife?

354
00:19:52,589 --> 00:19:53,939
是的
Yes.

355
00:19:54,569 --> 00:19:57,535
天哪 她肯定有很坚强的神经
My lord, she must have a nerve.

356
